body.description: CP2K32G56C46U5 is the Crucial 64GB kit consisting of (2) 32GB DDR5 Pro desktop module that operates at the speed of 5600MT/s and has a CAS Latency of 46. It is a UDIMM and conforms to the industry standard DDR5 UDIMM layout of 288 pins. It is compatible with systems that can take DDR5-5600 UDIMM memory.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Micron quality and reliability As one of only three global memory manufacturers, and with 45 years of memory expertise, Micron delivers cutting-edge engineering and superior component and module-level testing for all Crucial DRAM products. Only DDR5-enabled CPUs/motherboards support DDR5 memory. Not compatible with DDR4 motherboards.Crucial DDR5 desktop memory modules (UDIMMs) can reach rated speeds with Intel XMP 3.0 or AMD EXPO turned on in the UEFI/BIOS settings. Applicable for all Crucial DDR5 desktop memory (UDIMM) modules except Crucial DDR5-4800 desktop memory, which supports only Intel XMP 3.0. Based on published competitor specs for DDR5 memory as of August 2023. Altering clock frequency or voltage beyond advertised speeds and timing (overclocking) may result in damage to computer components. Micron disclaims any and all liability for such damage.DDR5 speeds are comparable to extreme-performance DDR4 memory speeds and, at 4,800MT/s, at least 1.5x faster than maximum standard DDR4 speeds of 3,200MT/s.Crucial DDR5 Pro Memory modules (UDIMMs) can only be installed in desktops/workstations built to support DDR5 DRAM, such as 12th and 13th Gen Intel Core and AMD Ryzen 7000 Series desktop processors.DDR5 data rate of 6,000MT/s transfers 1.88x the DDR4 data rate of 3,200MT/s.Under memory-intensive workloads, DDR5 can deliver up to 2x the bandwidth, per an internal simulation of dual ranked x8 modules in client platforms.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I am not trying to eke every last ounce of performance out of my PC. These RAM work great, are plenty fast, and seems reliable so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good RAM kit, but...
reviews.reviewText: This ram memory kit is slower than its competitors (It has 46 CL, which does not appear neither in the title nor description, it's a little slower, especially for gaming, although in the worst-case scenario the game may only run ~7 fps slower than it would with a memory with less CL, has no rgb and is aesthetically simple, however it is cheaper and of excellent quality, buying it on sale is a no brainer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Maxed Out My RAM
reviews.reviewText: After 13 years, I got a new desktop computer. I splurged and maxed out my RAM immediately. I decided to go with the Crucial Pro over the Corsair Vengeance mainly because I lucked out on a very cheap price during a small window of time during Black Friday, and because Crucial's website gave me the clear specifications I needed to know to make the appropriate decision.The only difference between the Pro and the regular version of this is the additional heatsink. Installation was easy as pie. Slide and snap the memory right into your motherboard. At boot up, your computer will (generally) alert you that your RAM amount has changed and will ask you to confirm that. Once my computer started up, I checked my system and it detected the correct amount at 64GB at my system's top 4800MT/s speed.I've been using it now for a month and have had no issues. My computer works great and I can do a lot (a lot) of things without any slowdown. Recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good DDR5 RAM kit!
reviews.reviewText: I got this one for under $70 during Black Friday, which is great deal; my new GIGABYTE B650 AERO G recognized it with no problem. I've been using it for a month at 5600MT/s without issues so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality performance 'no-frills' memory
reviews.reviewText: Installed these in my new Dell XPS 8960, replacing the 16GB of OEM DDR5-4800, and the BIOS recognized and configured the higher memory speeds automagically. Black heat spreaders are thankfully low-key.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024

reviews.reviewText: After a month testing.. RAM plays well with the MSI B760 Mortar WIFI board and an i5-12600K. No issues with XMP or timings.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Customer support was great.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this kit and one stick of the ram was bad which happens from time to time. When I contacted them about the ram being bad they send me a replacement before having me send the original order back. (if you build a computer and don't have any ram it won't work) so since that's how they handled it I can still use my computer in the meantime instead of it being a paperweight until I get the new ram. It's absolutely the best way they could have handled it. 10/10 will buy other parts from them in the future.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Dead on Arrival
reviews.reviewText: Occasionally I may buy a two pack of RAM where one stick is bad out of the box but I managed to win the lottery with my order as both 16 GB sticks of RAM in my 32 GB kit were defective right out of the box. Definitely disappointed. Also, the RMA process with Crucial is not all that user friendly and required talking with a real person to figure out as the return site would not accept the product id # from the RAM. It's unfortunate as I've not previously had issues with Crucial products where I've had to return it but now that I've had to deal with the return process I don't know if I want to risk it again.

There's not a whole lot to review about RAM, especially barebones RAM like this. There are no giant heatsinks, so it fits in tight places. There are no LEDs, so it's not flashy.But it was a great price and it works really well. Speeds are a little on the lower end for DDR5 that is still ramping up, but for now it's great.If you're looking for bang for buck, this is it.
Muy buen producto en especial por qué acepta las dos arquitecturas, "Amd EXPO" e Intel "XMP 3.0" funcionan perfecto.

reviews.reviewText: One of the cheaper DDR5 RAM out there with a great reputation for its stability and capability. If you want to OC then you may get better options from other retailers but for what crucial offers, it's very capable. Will be buying more crucial components in the future!
